  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Blood you spill tends to splatter. Creatures suffering from your bleed damage spill blood into any squares they occupy at the beginning of their turns, causing it to become slick and slippery. Moving into a square with slippery terrain requires a Reflex save to move at more than half speed for that action. Failure causes the creature to become flat-footed until the end of their turn, and stops their movement for that action. Failure by 5 or more causes the creature to fall prone and be considered flat-footed until the start of their next turn. Slippery terrain created by this talent dries up and becomes normal terrain after 10 minutes.</p>\n",
